This paper deals with a combinatorial market design problem and proposes a new solution concept called Combinatorial Walrasian Equilibrium (CWE). The paper discusses the algorithmic and economic aspects of the problem and provides strong results that hold for arbitrary valuations. Given the focus on market design and algorithmic aspects, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also deals with combinatorial optimization and approximation algorithms, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely sub-category. The use of valuation profiles and the algorithmic problem of social-welfare approximation suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses revenue extraction, which is a topic in cs.EC (Economics and Computation). Finally, the paper deals with lower bounds, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible sub-category.
